<link href="adcp.css" rel="stylesheet"><entry><xh5> make it up to someone • make it up with someone</xh5><p> <i>make it up to someone—</i>compensate a person for negligence, difficulties, inconvenience, etc.: If you’ll work overtime tonight, I’ll <u>make it up to</u> you by giving you Saturday morning off.</p><p> <i>make it up with someone</i>—(also: make up with someone) settle a quarrel; make one’s peace with a person: I really want to <u>make it up with</u> her, but she won’t speak to me.</p> </entry>
